cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with large-scale visual recognition tasks, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed Attribute-Based Synthetic Network (ABS-Net) is a neural network architecture that synthesizes pseudo feature representations, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of semantic attributes, which are related to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on a synthetic colored MNIST dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
